<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/11798503-l-legault">L. Legault</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">That isn&apos;t Deutsch, it&apos;s Dutch. Google translate says it means &apos;I&apos;m currently stuck. Does this matter to me? Wrong book at the wrong time? In any even<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">That isn't Deutsch, it's Dutch. Google translate says it means 'I'm currently stuck. Does this matter to me? Wrong book at the wrong time? In any event, efkes laid aside. Maybe after returning to the holidays. Anyone else who struggled with this?' Don't know what efkes is, and google doesn't either, it seems. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
