<div id="review_2370353387" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2370353387" />
    <a title="Bruce Beckham" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/28623020-bruce-beckham"><img alt="Bruce Beckham" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442874525p2/28623020.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2370353387?book_show_action=true">May 24, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bruce Beckham" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bruce Beckham" href="/user/show/28623020-bruce-beckham">Bruce Beckham</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2370353387" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9632529175391887828">This might be perverse logic, but having twice read <i>The Bridesmaid</i> I felt it was a safe bet for my introduction to audiobooks. This intuition proved correct – a rough knowledge of the plot helped me to pick up wherever I had left off – and it is such a good yarn that it didn’t spoil my enjoyment.<br/><br/>Mention Ruth Rendell and it’s tempting to think of Inspector Wexford, bucolic scenes and cosy cottages. Think again. <i>The Bridesmaid</i> is everything that isn’t in its title – a gripping concoction of urban </span>
  <span id="freeText9632529175391887828" style="display:none">This might be perverse logic, but having twice read <i>The Bridesmaid</i> I felt it was a safe bet for my introduction to audiobooks. This intuition proved correct – a rough knowledge of the plot helped me to pick up wherever I had left off – and it is such a good yarn that it didn’t spoil my enjoyment.<br /><br />Mention Ruth Rendell and it’s tempting to think of Inspector Wexford, bucolic scenes and cosy cottages. Think again. <i>The Bridesmaid</i> is everything that isn’t in its title – a gripping concoction of urban grit and gothic horror – a relentless rollercoaster of suspense, its locus a basement beneath London’s mean streets, where between soiled sheets sanity meets madness, and the onlooker must endure the agony and ecstasy to discover which will prevail.<br /><br />It’s a great read and – now – a great listen. I’m sold on audiobooks – so much more uplifting than the radio. But next month I must try something new!<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="9632529175391887828" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


