<div id="review_218411023" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/218411023" />
    <a title="Marian Allen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3314240-marian-allen"><img alt="Marian Allen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442500425p2/3314240.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/218411023?book_show_action=true">Oct 03, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Marian Allen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Marian Allen" href="/user/show/3314240-marian-allen">Marian Allen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer218411023" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6550683975475405151">There ought to be a two-tiered rating system, because this book was stylistically wonderful--atmospheric, evocative, kept me reading to the end. On the other hand, it had no plot and it didn&apos;t make a bit of sense. But, if you want to enjoy a really well-written exercise in style, and want to close the book and do something realfast before you have a chance to think about what you just read, this book will engage you, entertain you and haunt you. Once.</span>
  <span id="freeText6550683975475405151" style="display:none">There ought to be a two-tiered rating system, because this book was stylistically wonderful--atmospheric, evocative, kept me reading to the end. On the other hand, it had no plot and it didn't make a bit of sense. But, if you want to enjoy a really well-written exercise in style, and want to close the book and do something realfast before you have a chance to think about what you just read, this book will engage you, entertain you and haunt you. Once.</span>
