              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9887474200018753530">i usually LOVE ruth rendell&apos;s murder mysteries. this one was just weird. it spent too much tme in psychological buildup and motivation that didn&apos;t make sense to me. i don&apos;t recommend this book to anyone. (although from a critical standpoint i can appreciate the range of ruth&apos;s writing and am glad that it is not always the same predictable story every time and for that i will keep reading books by this author.) </span>
