<div id="review_2390447862" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2390447862" />
    <a title="Susan Blake" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/57168076-susan-blake"><img alt="Susan Blake" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2390447862?book_show_action=true">May 13, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Susan Blake" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Susan Blake" href="/user/show/57168076-susan-blake">Susan Blake</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/19417548-the-bridesmaid">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2390447862" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1737871474911698855"><strong>The Bridesmaid is a Weirdo</strong><br/><br/>As always, Rendell writes a psychological thriller that&apos;s absorbing and suspenseful, with interesting characters. The setting is present-day London, and to?e from character Phi!ilp&apos;s viewpoint. A very good read, although it feels like it ends abruptly, after having developed several subplots which apparently were superfluous to the story&apos;s conclusion.</span>
  <span id="freeText1737871474911698855" style="display:none"><strong>The Bridesmaid is a Weirdo</strong><br /><br />As always, Rendell writes a psychological thriller that's absorbing and suspenseful, with interesting characters. The setting is present-day London, and to?e from character Phi!ilp's viewpoint. A very good read, although it feels like it ends abruptly, after having developed several subplots which apparently were superfluous to the story's conclusion.</span>
